ap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/01 6:32:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: full speed quad kiting</span><hr size=1> I used to full speed kite early (level 30-40) .. then I discovered just how much safer BoF/Shackle kiting is. It took me a long time to figure out how to get stragglers and then repack the mobs in a timely/mana saving manor and all before snare broke.<br><br>Everyone says its 'so easy' ... but honestly it is, only after PRACTICE though. Soon full speed won't be an option. Soon CoF won't be enough to kill mobs either. Starting at 51 quading get so much more fun.<br><br>However, back to my point of practicing. Eventually you'll have to snare kite them. Practice with one, two then three. I was tri-kiting for quite a while, because if 1 split off from snare it was much easier that 2, ... if mana was low and you had just one straggler, you could root and med.<br><br>For me anyway 3 was a significant achievement. It wasn't until I continued to gain +mana gear and gain levels that I started to notice after 3 I still had a bub of mana or more. This meant 4 was possible.<br><br>Now I'm a quad kiting fool with mana AND harvest to spare in most cases. <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.bigjaco.com/SG/eq_screenies/vort_sig52.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://keith.vaughan.home.mindspring.com/img/ball3.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 9:25:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> yes.</span><hr size=1> I used to do full speed kiting around that level range as well.  The difficulty at higher level is that the mobs that have the noticible exp run VERY fast.  And if I'm using Pillars, interrupts or SELF-hits would be common.<br><br>The only full speed pulling I do now is Raptors, and that is only because pulling over the water before snaring them functions as a natural snare until you cast BoF.  Other than that, I'm open to suggestions.<br><br>W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=29.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=29.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=29.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.threadControl?topicID=29.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/